PURGE_ARCHIVE_MAX_TOTAL_ATTACHMENT_BYTES=25165824
PURGE_MAX_MESSAGES=1000
PURGE_MAX_SCAN=3000

# If you've moved the Java music sidecar into this repo, keep the folder name
# `rumi-music-service` inside the `rumi/` folder (path: `rumi/rumi-music-service`).
# The worker Dockerfile has been updated to build from that location so no
# additional env var is required for the build context.
#
# Runtime notes:
# - `RUMI_MUSIC_SERVICE_URL` is the internal URL the Node bot uses to call the
#   local sidecar (defaults to `http://127.0.0.1:3025`).
# - `RUMI_MUSIC_SERVICE_PUBLIC_URL` should be set to a public HTTPS URL if you
#   expose the music service externally (required for Spotify OAuth callbacks).
# - `SPOTIFY_REDIRECT_URI` must be a publicly reachable HTTPS URL registered in
#   your Spotify developer app and typically points to
#   `${RUMI_MUSIC_SERVICE_PUBLIC_URL}/api/spotify/callback`.
# - For the temporary embedded Lavalink, `LAVALINK_URL`/`LAVALINK_PASSWORD` are
#   already set to local defaults compatible with the worker image.
#
# Dashboard hosting notes:
# - `PUBLIC_SITE_URL` should point at the public marketing site host.
# - `STUDIO_URL` / `DASHBOARD_FRONTEND_URL` should point at the studio path.
# - The dashboard backend now serves the authenticated studio from `/studio`
#   on the same host instead of a separate subdomain.
